title: 3:10 to Yuma
description: An update of the 1957 Western, 3:10 TO YUMA pairs an infamous outlaw and the struggling rancher who volunteers to deliver him to justice.

title: Casino Royale
description: After earning 00 status and a licence to kill, Secret Agent James Bond sets out on his first mission as 007. Bond must defeat a private banker funding terrorists in a high-stakes game of poker at Casino Royale, Montenegro.
starring: Daniel Craig, Eva Green, Judi Dench

title: Cats & Dogs
description: A look at the top-secret, high-tech espionage war going on between cats and dogs, which their human owners are blissfully unaware of.

title: El Camino Hacia El Dorado
description: Al desembarcar en las playas de El Dorado, Tulio, Miguel son confundidos con dioses y son adorados con riquezas. Deben decidir entre huir con el oro o  salvar a los pobladores de El Dorado.

title: Free Fall
description: It’s been called the German Brokeback Mountain for its portrayal of forbidden love between two police cadets as previously heterosexual Marc (Hanno Koffler) and fellow male cop Kay (Max Riemelt) embark on an unexpected life-changing affair.

title: Hard Night Falling
description: Goro, a criminal mastermind, plots to steal a massive cache of gold from the billionaire businessman Rossini.

title: Legend of the Guardians The Owls of Ga'Hoole
description: A courageous owl launches a quest to locate the legendary defenders who can save the owl species in this animated adventure.

title: Lucky Day
description: After being released from prison, a safecracker tries to protect his family from a psychopathic contract killer who's seeking revenge.

title: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
description: Russell Crowe is a 19th-century British warship captain who leads a motley crew as they prepare to attack a superior French vessel.

title: The Peanut Butter Falcon
description: Shia LaBeouf, Dakota Johnson, and Zack Gottsagen star in "a modern-day Mark Twain fable that will melt your heart" (Flickering Myth).

title: Primal
description: Frank's caught wildlife in the Brazilian jungle incl. a 400 lbs. white jaguar. He ships it on the same ship as an arrested assassin. The assassin breaks free and frees the animals.

title: Quantum of Solace
description: James Bond descends into mystery as he tries to stop a mysterious organisation from eliminating a country's most valuable resource.

title: Red
description: Retired assassins are targeted for death in this comic action adventure.

title: Rustlers' Rhapsody
description: Rex O'Herlihan, The Singing Cowboy, finds himself in a cliché town where an evil cattle baron and some new cowboys conspire to force sheep ranchers out of their valley.

title: Safe
description: Mei, a young girl whose memory holds a priceless numerical code, finds herself pursued by the Triads, the Russian mob, and corrupt NYC cops. Coming to her aid is an ex-cage fighter whose life was destroyed by the gangsters on Mei's trail.

title: The Saint
description: Want someone to infiltrate a top-secret organiz ation or steal a scientific formula that could change the world? For the right price, The Saint's your man.

title: Spy Kids: All the Time in the World
description: Marissa Cortez Wilson (Jessica Alba) is a retired spy who keeps that identity hidden from her clueless husband and whip-smart twin stepchildren, Rebecca (Rowan Blanchard) and Cecil (Mason Cook). However, when a villain called Timekeeper (Jeremy Piven) threatens to conquer the world, Marissa springs back into action as head of the OSS, home of the now-defunct Spy Kids Division. With help from some cool gadgets and two former spy kids, Rebecca and Cecil join the fight to save Earth.

title: Teen Titans Go! Vs. Teen Titans
description: An antagonist forces the 2003 and 2013 teams to battle to prove which team is superior.

title: Top Gun
description: Devil-may-care navy pilot Pete Mitchell (Tom Cruise) is sent to Miramar Naval Air Station for advanced training. Here he vies with Tom Kasansky (Val Kilmer) for the coveted "Top Gun" award.

title: Ultraviolet
description: Milla Jovovich, Cameron Bright, Nick Chinlund and William Fichtner star in this story of a woman caught in a futuristic civil war between the government and a subculture of disease modified humans in whom speed, strength and intelligence are magnified.

title: Australia
description: Nicole Kidman and Hugh Jackman star in this sweeping epic about an English woman who finds tragedy, danger and passion in Australia.

title: Dora and the Lost City of Gold
description: Having spent most of her life exploring the jungle, nothing could prepare Dora for her most dangerous adventure yet -- high school. Accompanied by a ragtag group of teens and Boots the monkey, Dora embarks on a quest to save her parents while trying to solve the seemingly impossible mystery behind a lost Incan civilization.

title: Bernie the Dolphin 2
description: The kids are thrilled that Bernie has come back. But so has their old enemy Winston, who's about to kidnap the talented dolphin. Kevin and Holly must rescue their splashy friend before it's too late.

title: Between Us
description: Longtime couple Henry (Ben Feldman) and Dianne (Olivia Thirlby) are afraid that if they finally tie the knot it will lead to the end of their days as free-spirited urbanites. But a whirlwind night apart, involving temptations from a duo of strangers, will either make them realize why they are together in the first place or finally drive them apart forever.

title: The Brothers McMullen
description: Three Irish-Catholic brothers deal with their respective lady troubles in Edward Burns' acclaimed indie film.

title: City Slickers
description: Billy Crystal, Daniel Stern and Jack Palance star as three middle-aged men experiencing midlife crises, who embark on an adventure to find renewal and purpose.

title: Death at a Funeral
description: Things go haywire when the members of a dysfunctional family gather for the funeral of one of their own in this dark comedy.

title: Four Weddings and a Funeral
description: A reserved Englishman meets attractive American Carrie at a wedding and falls in love with her, but his inability to express his feelings seems to forestall any possibility of relationship.

title: Gayby
description: "Gayby" is an irreverent comedy about friendship, growing older, sex, loneliness, and the family you chose.

title: A Good Woman
description: In 1930s Italy, a notorious seductress sets her sights on a wealthy businessman, while his new bride is pursued by a rakish playboy.

title: Hateship Loveship
description: A wild teenage girl orchestrates a romance between her nanny and her father, who is a recovering addict. Stars Kristen Wiig and Guy Pearce.

title: Hurricane Bianca
description: A teacher from New York moves to a small town in Texas and is quickly fired for being gay. He soon returns dressed as a mean lady to get revenge on the nasty townspeople.

title: La Boda de Mi Mejor Amigo
description: Jules Potter, se da cuenta de que está enamorada de su mejor amigo, Michael. Aunque hay un problema: él está a punto de casarse. Cómicamente enloquecida y llena de proyectos retorcidos, Jules hará lo que sea para recuperarlo... excepto contarle la verdad.

title: Letters to Juliet
description: In modern Verona, where women seeking their Romeos leave letters to Juliet, a young writer (Amanda Seyfried) finds a life-altering 50-year-old letter.

title: Match
description: Patrick Stewart stars as a master dance teacher and choreographer with a lifetime of memories, who is interviewed by a young couple and unexpectedly forced to confront the painful decisions he thought he left in the past.

title: Rain Man
description: The 1988 Oscar(R)-winner with Dustin Hoffman as an autistic man who is taken on an impromptu road trip by his brother (Tom Cruise).

title: Sordid Lives
description: In this cult classic comedy from writer-director Del Shores, a gay West Hollywood actor returns home to his small Texas town for his grandmother’s funeral.

title: Stuck on You
description: Conjoined twins head for Hollywood so one can take his shot at acting stardom in this amusing Farrelly Brothers comedy.

title: Tales from the Golden Age
description: With both humor and outrage, five ordinary people fight to hold onto freedom, love and laughter as their lives are turned upside down by the 1980s Romanian communist regime.

title: The Trip to Greece
description: Funnymen Steve Coogan and Rob Brydon travel to restaurants, hotels and ancient landmarks in Greece.
Jack O'Connell is a British solider accidentally abandoned on the streets of Belfast in 1971. Alone, he must survive the night within enemy lines.

title: Were The World Mine
description: If you had a love-potion, who would you make fall madly in love with you? Timothy, prone to escaping his dismal high school reality through dazzling musical daydreams, gets to answer that question in a very real way.

title: Alive and Kicking
description: After getting involved in swing dancing, some people are inspired to look inside themselves and make changes in their lives.

title: Killing for Love
description: What could drive an innocent man to take the fall for a crime he didn't commit? A shocking true tale of obsessive love, betrayal, and murder.

title: Nick Nolte: No Exit
description: Actor Nick Nolte interviews himself.

title: Pigeon Kings
description: Pigeons do somersaults in mid-flight, and there is a subculture of men in South Central L.A. devoted to this phenomenon as a competitive sport. The former champion mentors an up-and-comer, and together they prepare for the World Cup.

title: Slay the Dragon
description: Activists work to rid gerrymandering from America's election process.

title: Unacknowledged: An Exposé of the Greatest Secret in Human History
description: Disclosure Project founder Dr. Steven M. Greer offers evidence of extraterrestrial contact, including top-secret testimonials, documents and never-before-seen UFO footage.

title: Bull
description: On the outskirts of Houston, a teen reeling from her mom’s incarceration and an aging bullfighter struggling to keep a foothold in the rodeo circuit, form an unlikely bond and attempt to right their own paths.

title: The Cup
description: The inspirational true story of horse racing legend who overcame incredible odds to win the 2002 Melbourne Cup Trophy.

title: Daffodils
description: A bittersweet love story told through enchanting re-imaginings of popular and iconic New Zealand songs.

title: Day Night Day Night
description: An anonymous young woman arrives in Manhattan on a bus. She receives numerous calls on her cell phone and proceeds to a hotel room. Assisted by various handlers, she prepares for her mission: to detonate a bomb in Times Square. She walks the city streets, but the time of her attack -- and thus that of her own death -- remains unknown.

title: The Edukators
description: Peter (Stipe Erceg) and Jan (Daniel Brühl) are "edukators," anarchists who break into wealthy people's homes -- never stealing, but serving notice to fatcats that their days are numbered. Along comes Jule (Julia Jentsch), a poor student and Peter's girlfriend, who convinces Jan to help her edukate a businessman (Burghart Klaussner) she owes money to. When Jule mistakenly leaves evidence behind, they must go back to the crime scene, where they are surprised and events quickly get out of hand.

title: Elena Undone
description: Fate brings two diversely different women together, and sets them on a collision course that will shatter their preconceived notions about love, life and the power of one's soul

title: The Flood
description: An immigration officer must interrogate an asylum seeker to see if he's lying.

title: Goodnight Mommy
description: In this terrifying thriller, twin boys play a dangerous game of make-believe that blurs the line between nightmare and reality as they start to doubt whether their mother, recovering from cosmetic surgery, is really who she says she is.

title: Love Songs
description: An independent and cheerful widow recalls her life in the late 60s.  A story filled with idealism and poetry, her failed relationship, her forced marriage, being a young widow and a single mother during the rise of the naxalite movement.

title: Margin Call
description: Employees at an investment bank scheme to keep their firm from ruin in the early days of the 2008 financial crisis in this riveting drama.

title: Monster's Ball
description: Halle Berry won the 2001 Best Actress Oscar for her portrayal of a black waitress who falls in love with a racist white prison guard.

title: The Necessities of Life
description: A moving and inspiring story about an unlikely friendship between two lonely souls who discover a renewed passion for life.

title: Ordinary Love
description: Joan and Tom are an everyday couple with a remarkable love. When Joan is diagnosed with breast cancer, the course of her treatment shines a light on their enduring devotion, as they must find the humor and grace to survive a year of adversity.

title: A Perfect Murder
description: A wealthy woman becomes the target for murder when her husband, an investor with financial difficulties, discovers her affair with an artist and blackmails her lover into killing her.

title: Pit Stop
description: In this perfectly crafted American drama, openly gay Ernesto and closeted Gabe grapple with the trials and tribulations of being gay in a small, working-class Texas town.

title: Romeo & Juliet
description: Hailee Steinfeld and Douglas Booth star as Shakespeare's star-crossed lovers whose feuding families stand in the way of their happiness.

title: Sleeping with the Enemy
description: In this tense thriller, a battered wife (Julia Roberts) stages her death, moves, and assumes a new identity – only to be threatened again once her husband learns of the ruse.

title: Spare Parts
description: George Lopez leads a winning cast in this inspiring true story about four high-school students who defy the odds in a competition against the nation's top universities

title: Spring Forward
description: Trying to put himself back together after serving prison time for robbery, Paul (Liev Schreiber) takes a job as a parks employee in a small Connecticut town. His co-worker, Murph (Ned Beatty), a generation older than Paul, is dealing with his own issues, chiefly the the impending death of his very ill son. After the men have a run-in with local snob Frederickson (Campbell Scott), Murph's age and experience starts to temper Paul's fiery nature, as the younger man begins to embrace his new life.

title: Stanley & Iris
description: Jane Fonda and Robert De Niro star in a touching story of two people who escape their own private prisons -- he can't read, she's still grieving for her dead husband -- to explore a tender relationship.

title: Behind You
description: Two young sisters find that all the mirrors in her house are covered or hidden. When one of the sisters happens upon a mirror in the basement, she unknowingly releases a malicious demon that had haunted her mother and aunt years ago.

title: Blood Diner
description: Two brothers (Rick Burks, Carl Crew) running a diner collect body parts needed to bring an ancient goddess to life.

title: Child's Play
description: A killer sought by a Chicago detective becomes a doll called Chucky, bought by a woman for her son.

title: Dark Touch
description: In a remote Irish village, police are called to the scene of a massacre, but they ignore the lone survivor's claim that the house was responsible for the carnage.

title: The Devil's Candy
description: An artist and his family think they've moved into the house of their dreams, but when he is possessed by a mysterious dark force the family must fight to save their souls.

title: Exorcismus
description: Spanish horror film about a fifteen year old girl who falls prey to a series of seizures that leave doctors baffled, forcing her parents to summon a priest to deal with the sinister forces lurking within her.

title: Hellraiser
description: From horror master Clive Barker comes this chilling nightmare featuring the first appearance of the hideous Pinhead.

title: My Bloody Valentine
description: A crazed miner returns from deep within the bowels of a dark tunnel with a pick in his hand and revenge in his heart.

title: The Shrine
description: The search for a missing teen in Poland leads a rookie reporter (Cindy Sampson) and her companions to an encounter with deadly cultists.

title: Spiderhole
description: A young artist (Emma Griffiths Malin) and her friends find terror lurking in the shadows of an abandoned London home when they move in as squatters.

title: Stir of Echoes
description: A man (Kevin Bacon) beings having disturbing visions that lead him on an obsessive search for answers in this scary ghost story.

title: City Slickers II: The Legend of Curly's Gold
description: Three urban buddies trek to the Wild West seeking a fortune in lost gold.

title: The Wretched
description: A rebellious teenage boy embarks on a gutsy crusade to stop the terrifying evil he suspects has possessed his neighbor in this bone-chilling occult thriller.

title: Life Like
description: A couple's perception of humanity is changed by a lifelike robot.

title: Company Business
description: The CIA reactivates agent Sam Boyd (Gene Hackman) to conduct a secret exchange of prisoners in post-wall Berlin. While Boyd escorts his former KGB adversary, Pyotr Grushenko (Mikhail Baryshnikov), to the rendezvous, the unlikely duo is tipped off that they are being set up. When the aging former cold warriors realize they are in over their heads, they enlist the help of beautiful Natasha Grimaud (Geraldine Danon) to help them evade the forces bent on sacrificing them.

title: ThunderCats (1985)
description: From beyond any known galaxy, bringing with them the laws and ideals of their green planet, Thundera, come the ThunderCats!

title: ThunderCats (2011)
description: ThunderCats, ho! Warner Bros. Animation (WBA) is reimagining the 1980s animated action classic in an all-new animated series combining swords and science and boasting ferocious battles with the highest of stakes.

title: Mega Hammerhead: Ultimate Predator
description: Great hammerhead sharks are expanding their range and coming closer to shore. Here, Dr Neil Hammerschlag is diving in to find out why.

title: Savage Kingdom
description: Three thousand square miles of remote African Savannah this ancient land is governed by competing clans of ruthlessly proficient predators. Each day is a life and death struggle – animal against animal, animal against nature. Savute is a land where natural law is taken to its limit and sometimes... beyond. It has always been this way. Like a lion with a wildebeest, this six-part drama takes the viewer by the throat in a bitter, sweet embrace of life and death and refuses to let go until the final curtain.

title: Shark vs. Surfer
description: Accounts of shark attacks on surfers; caught-on-camera encounters, and interviews with the victims; insight from marine biologists Ryan Johnson and Dr. Stephen Kajiura.

title: Shark vs. Whale
description: A drone films a humpback whale being strategically drowned by a great white shark; marine biologist Ryan Johnson explores how and why great white sharks become whale killers.

title: Sharks of the Bermuda Triangle
description: Marine biologist Dr. Austin Gallagher searches for the holy grail of shark research -- the secret breeding grounds of tiger sharks.

title: United Sharks of America: Shark Bite Capitals
description: Some of the most beautiful beaches in the United States also feature the highest incidences of shark encounters.

title: What the Shark?
description: A look at sharks living deep in the ocean, where extreme adaptation is critical to survival.

title: Auditions
description: Actors suffer the indignity of auditioning. Presented by Cake on FX.

title: Brassic
description: Vinnie, a Lancashire lad with bipolar disorder, and Dylan, his razor-smart best mate, are inseparable and utterly co-dependant. But Dylan's girlfriend Erin might just shake things up for good with her plans to leave town and start a new life for herself and her kid, Tyler. Dylan is faced with the impossible decision between a fresh start with the love of his life or staying behind with his inseparable gang of mates that he can't live without.

title: Dicktown
description: Welcome to Richardsville, NC (aka DICKTOWN to the locals), its famous boy detective, John Hunchman, and his hired muscle, David Purefoy. Except they're not boys any more and while they're still detectives, they still only solve crimes for teenagers. Presented by Cake on FX.

title: The Kids Are Alright
description: Set in the 1970s, this ensemble comedy follows a traditional Irish-Catholic family, the Clearys, as they navigate big and small changes during one of America’s most turbulent decades. In a working-class neighborhood outside Los Angeles, Mike and Peggy raise eight boisterous boys who live out their days with little supervision. The household is turned upside down as the times are changing and this family will never be the same. There are 10 people, three bedrooms, one bathroom and everyone in it for themselves.

title: Odeon
description: A sneak peek into the lives of different individuals in a world known as ODEON. Presented by Cake on FX.

title: Walt
description: An animated series that follows a small, egg-shaped creature named Walt as he struggles with ordinary life in New York City. Presented by Cake on FX.

title: Bake You Rich
description: Four professional bakers compete for a chance to hit the big time and have their unique creations produced and sold online by the Cake Boss.

title: Worst Bakers in America
description: Twelve of the worst bakers in America get drafted into baking boot camp with Chef Duff Goldman and Chef Lorraine Pascale. They have six weeks to go from fakers to bakers as they compete in a series of challenges to win $25,000!

title: Murder in Paradise
description: Vacation in paradise, or is it? MURDER IN PARADISE is a mystery series where dream getaways are torn apart by a horrific murder. Were victims the random targets of a brutal stranger or the focused objects of premeditated evil?

title: Dear America
description: Based on the best-selling Scholastic books; Dear America features the rich and spirited stories of fictional teenage women at various turning points in American history. The hopes and dreams, trials and tribulations of a time period are captured by each young woman’s unique voice.

title: El embarcadero
description: High-profile architect Alexandra faces her worst nightmare when she gets a call from local cop Conrado to identify her husband Oscar's body, found on a pier. She soon finds out there was more to his life than she knew.

title: In My Skin
description: The coming-of-age story of 16-year-old Bethan as she deals with comical and painful insecurities of teenage life.

title: Love in the Time of Corona
description: An ensemble of characters shelter in their homes during the COVID-19 pandemic, some of whom are wondering if a hookup with a roommate can ever be casual, while another is kicking herself for deciding to isolate with an ex.

title: The Royal Diaries
description: The Royal Diaries offer a fictional look into the lives of young royal girls throughout history. The hopes and dreams, trials and tribulations of the time periods are captured by each young woman’s unique voice.

title: Blippi
description: Explore the world as seen through the eyes of a curious toddler. Feed your kids’ curiosity while they learn about vehicles, animals, the natural world and so much more. Blippi helps children‘s understanding of the world and encourages vocabulary development. Blippi loves visiting exciting places such as children’s museums and the zoo! He loves singing, dancing, playing and exploring.

title: Chef Out Of Water
description: A Chef must create a stunning and delicious 3-course meal despite being forced to cook using unconventional methods.

title: Christina on the Coast
description: Real estate and flipping expert Christina Anstead helps clients transform their outdated properties into high-end homes in Southern California. She also begins a personal journey as she looks for a new home for her family.

title: Honeymoon Hunters
description: Fun-loving couple Ben and Maggie check out three different locations for their perfect getaway. Between St. Thomas, Costa Rica and Miami Beach, which one will they choose to fit their budget and also create a memorable trip?

title: Island Life
description: Buyers search for an island home.

title: Mediterranean Life
description: In search of a peaceful, healthy lifestyle filled with sun-drenched beaches and gorgeous weather, potential homeowners shop for houses along the Mediterranean Sea.

title: Celebrating John Lewis: Civil Rights Icon
description: Funeral service for Rep. John Lewis held in Atlanta: President Barack Obama delivers the eulogy; Presidents George W. Bush and Bill Clinton were among the attendees.

title: The Democratic National Convention -- Your Voice/Your Vote 2020
description: George Stephanopoulos, David Muir and Linsey Davis lead coverage of the election year event during which delegates select the party's nominees for president and vice president.

title: Mission Overview: NASA’s Perseverance Mars Rover
description: NASA's Mars 2020 Perseverance Rover is heading to the Red Planet to search for signs of ancient life, collect samples for future return to Earth and help pave the way for human exploration.

title: NASA Science Live: Perseverance Mars Rover & the Search for Ancient Life
description: There’s evidence that the Red Planet was much wetter and warmer, with a thicker atmosphere, billions of years ago. Could it also have supported life?

title: Larry King Now
description: Legendary broadcaster Larry King brings his unique brand of talk online, interviewing the day's most fascinating newsmakers, celebrities, world leaders and internet stars as only Larry can.

title: Spoilers With Kevin Smith
description: Watch "Spoilers", Kevin Smith's movie "revue." Spoilers is a multi-act film extravaganza mixing lively group chats, interviews with movie and pop culture icons, animated shorts and cinematic reenactments. Each week, Kevin, a special guest and movie lovers passionately sound off on the year's most anticipated summer blockbusters, breaking down their favorite scenes and what should have been left on the cutting room floor.

title: The View
description: 'The View' is the place to be heard with live broadcasts five days a week co-hosted by Whoopi Goldberg, Joy Behar, Sunny Hostin, and Meghan McCain.
